FBIS4-9986 "drlat066_o_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 Colombia Pastrana Demands Investigation of Wiretapping Pastrana Demands Investigation of Wiretapping PA0604041194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 5 Apr 94 PA0604041194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours Newscast"] [Text] Andres Pastrana Arango, New Democratic Force's presidential candidate, demanded a thorough investigation of the delicate wiretapping incident reported by the SEMANA magazine. [Begin recording] [Pastrana] The incident is very serious. The country expects it to be clarified. We cannot understand how a group as important as the Santo Domingo Group can be involved in wiretapping, as the magazine reported. Today, the country demands an explanation. It is important to clarify this problem. [Reporter] Will the government intervene? [Pastrana] It should. Reports have been filed with the attorney general. [end recording]
